# Catalog Unit Governance Rule

When changing reusable UI units, maintain the unified `Catalog` menu and previews.

## Must Follow
- Use `src/descriptions/unitDefinitions.ts` as the single source of truth.
- Keep unit taxonomy in `Catalog`: `components`, `blocks`, `pageTypes`.
- Show only items where `renderable === true` and `usedInPrototype === true`.
- If a unit cannot be rendered yet, do not expose it in the menu.

## Required Updates In Same Task
- Update unit metadata in `src/descriptions/unitDefinitions.ts`.
- Update preview rendering in `src/pages/catalog/Catalog/Catalog.page.tsx`.
- Keep `/descriptions` redirected to `/catalog` (no split maintenance).

## Validation
- Tabs and search in `Catalog` remain functional.
- No conceptual-only entries shown without renderable UI.
